description: Tabulated Boys function data generated by Fred Manby in Mathematica. The data is for Fn(x), with 0 < x < 15. There are 151 sets of 33 datapoints, where set 0 is for x = 0 and subsequent sets are for x = n / 10, e.g. set 12 is for x = 12 / 10 = 1.2. The terms in each set are Boys functions Fn(x), where n=0 to 32, and these can be used in a Taylor expansion for Fn(x + deltaX), see Molecular Electronic-Structure Theory, p.367, Eq. 9.8.12. Since n = 0 to 32, the maximum n which can be expanded in a given Taylor expansion is 33-ntaylor, where ntaylor is the number of terms in the Taylor expansion. To maintain the full precision of data when being processed in Python, the data are stored as strings and manipulated as strings -- this avoids any double precision rounding errors during the code generation phase. If xmin == '0', then xmin is assumed to be exactly zero by the Boys function generation code.
